rComments: Fantastic prof who is really enthusiastic & knowledgeable about the material. You can tell he really cares and that is contagious! Wonderful & challenging lab experience that was relevant to class material. Tests were difficult but manageable if you paid attention in class. Grading was very fair. A really helpful nice guy to converse with as well.
Well, I loved the course. I especially enjoyed the labs, in which we were able to work on our own time.

The first half of the course was well laid out, and the first test properly represented the course material we had covered. The second test strayed somewhat, and I found it very difficult, and the course notes, which had been posted at the beginning of the year were not regularly posted in the second half of the course.
who bell-curves tests in a class of 30 (read: hard)? worst botany class ever, and i've taken many of them

He's nice when u ask questions (if he doesn't give u an annoyed look first), but that's it. Lab takes up too much of ur time (plus the 3 hrs weekly). Marking is arbitrary. Tests HARD & not well written. THE CLASS NEVER KNOWS WHAT TO DO B/C HE DOESN'T GIVE CLEAR DIRECTIONS. He's a researcher, not a teacher. Keep up ur GPA - stay away from the course
